# Append-only logbook files.
#
# Two agents (cloud on claude/* branches, local on master) both append handoff
# notes to CLAUDE.md section 6 and rows to the COLLAB-PROTOCOL.md work registry.
# The actual code never collides (each tool is its own cmd/ + internal/ dir), but
# these two text files collided on EVERY non-fast-forward merge — which is exactly
# what made the one-click "Get Becky Updates" button punt to the assistant every
# time once more than one cloud branch was waiting.
#
# git's built-in `union` merge driver resolves an overlapping change by keeping
# BOTH sides' lines instead of raising a conflict. For append-only narrative logs
# that is the correct behaviour: nobody loses a handoff note, and the button can
# merge unattended. (Tradeoff: if both sides edit the *same existing* line, union
# keeps both copies — a visible duplicate a human can trim, never a lost edit.)
CLAUDE.md            merge=union
COLLAB-PROTOCOL.md   merge=union
